00:58:54,907 --> 00:58:56,636
- This isn't easy.
- I know, right?

1298
00:58:56,637 --> 00:58:59,007
(Shin Jae Hyuk and Yoon Hoo, the men's room beside the entrance)

1299
00:59:00,617 --> 00:59:02,847
(Knocking)

1300
00:59:02,947 --> 00:59:04,416
I have nothing to do.

1301
00:59:04,417 --> 00:59:05,887
We also...

1302
00:59:06,287 --> 00:59:08,586
Did you unpack or...

1303
00:59:08,587 --> 00:59:09,916
(Ding dong)

1304
00:59:09,917 --> 00:59:11,286
- That...
- How...

1305
00:59:11,287 --> 00:59:12,357
(Startled)

1306
00:59:12,957 --> 00:59:13,957
Someone's coming.

1307
00:59:14,357 --> 00:59:16,027
- A parcel?
- Who would join already?

1308
00:59:16,357 --> 00:59:17,626
Is the latecomer already here?

1309
00:59:17,627 --> 00:59:20,497
- No way.
- They wouldn't join so fast.

1310
00:59:20,837 --> 00:59:22,497
- Joon Soo would definitely come.
- This...

1311
00:59:23,837 --> 00:59:26,536
There must be a reason you're here.

1312
00:59:26,537 --> 00:59:27,806
That's true.

1313
00:59:27,807 --> 00:59:29,537
It's game over once Joon Soo joins.

1314
00:59:32,307 --> 00:59:33,646
What... Goodness.

1315
00:59:33,647 --> 00:59:35,346
(Who rang the bell?)

1316
00:59:35,347 --> 00:59:36,647
Something's here.

1317
00:59:42,157 --> 00:59:43,686
What's this?

1318
00:59:43,687 --> 00:59:46,087
- Gosh, what's this?
- Christmas presents?

1319
00:59:46,487 --> 00:59:48,757
- Goodness.
- It's Christmas today.

1320
00:59:48,857 --> 00:59:50,056
Presents?

1321
00:59:50,057 --> 00:59:51,366
It's already Christmas.

1322
00:59:51,367 --> 00:59:52,596
Could Joon Soo be in there?

1323
00:59:52,597 --> 00:59:53,936
Will Joon Soo appear from there?

1324
00:59:53,937 --> 00:59:56,167
He could appear like this.

1325
00:59:56,597 --> 00:59:57,806
It must be tough in there, Joon Soo.

1326
00:59:57,807 --> 00:59:59,506
- That's possible.
- He's so tall too.

1327
00:59:59,507 --> 01:00:01,276
- Ta-da.
- He's tall.

1328
01:00:01,277 --> 01:00:02,407
(They keep being suspicious of Joon Soo making an appearance.)

1329
01:00:03,377 --> 01:00:05,207
- Can you carry it yourself?
- Let me help.

1330
01:00:05,407 --> 01:00:06,477
I'll hold the top.

1331
01:00:08,917 --> 01:00:10,487
She's strong.

1332
01:00:11,187 --> 01:00:12,686
- Here.
- Yu Bin is strong.

1333
01:00:12,687 --> 01:00:14,656
She's strong.

1334
01:00:14,657 --> 01:00:15,917
Yes.

1335
01:00:16,017 --> 01:00:18,026
Why isn't Jae Seung helping out?

1336
01:00:18,027 --> 01:00:21,297
(He can only laugh.)

1337
01:00:22,157 --> 01:00:23,196
We got a letter.

1338
01:00:23,197 --> 01:00:25,327
(And a letter arrived too.)

1339
01:00:27,297 --> 01:00:29,797
"Split up into teams and perform these tasks."

1340
01:00:30,467 --> 01:00:32,707
"Cooking and decorating Christmas trees."

1341
01:00:33,467 --> 01:00:34,876
It's not a 2-on-2.

1342
01:00:34,877 --> 01:00:37,077
(3-on-3 mini date)

1343
01:00:37,277 --> 01:00:39,676
It could be 2 men and 1 woman...

1344
01:00:39,677 --> 01:00:41,346
- or 2 women and 1 man.
- That's right.

1345
01:00:41,347 --> 01:00:43,146
- They'll be mixed.
- Exactly.

1346
01:00:43,147 --> 01:00:46,346
They can spend time with those they're interested in...

1347
01:00:46,347 --> 01:00:48,156
- That's it.
- and appeal to them naturally.

1348
01:00:48,157 --> 01:00:49,456
- That's right.
- It's a good opportunity.

1349
01:00:49,457 --> 01:00:50,886
It's game over then.

1350
01:00:50,887 --> 01:00:52,386
(Looking forward to it)

1351
01:00:52,387 --> 01:00:54,927
- Three on each team.
- Two tasks?

1352
01:00:55,257 --> 01:00:56,257
Three on each team.

1353
01:00:57,927 --> 01:01:00,497
We're finally starting.

1354
01:01:00,667 --> 01:01:03,636
I wanted to be on the same team as Yoon Hoo.

1355
01:01:03,637 --> 01:01:05,136
My gosh.

1356
01:01:05,137 --> 01:01:06,207
Good.

1357
01:01:08,107 --> 01:01:09,177
Yoon Hoo.

1358
01:01:09,677 --> 01:01:12,347
- I wanted to work with him.
- Of course you'd want that.

1359
01:01:12,907 --> 01:01:14,046
Yoon Hoo is popular.

1360
01:01:14,047 --> 01:01:15,777
Hoo is very popular.

1361
01:01:18,417 --> 01:01:21,457
I want to be on the same team as Si Woo.

1362
01:01:30,827 --> 01:01:33,527
- Are they reading the room?
- They can't take the initiative.

1363
01:01:35,967 --> 01:01:38,337
I heard you liked cooking.

1364
01:01:39,067 --> 01:01:40,207
I see.

1365
01:01:41,577 --> 01:01:42,577
Meat...

1366
01:01:42,577 --> 01:01:43,577
(You said you were good at cooking meat.)

1367
01:01:43,607 --> 01:01:45,306
Meat?

1368
01:01:45,307 --> 01:01:46,447
(Yoon Hoo ends up in the cooking team.)

1369
01:01:47,077 --> 01:01:49,046
- Meat?
- Meat? I'll make pasta.

1370
01:01:49,047 --> 01:01:50,346
Pasta?

1371
01:01:50,347 --> 01:01:51,717
- She joined immediately.
- She said pasta.

1372
01:01:52,047 --> 01:01:54,186
- Pasta?
- She joins him by saying pasta.

1373
01:01:54,187 --> 01:01:56,116
(Cooking team, Yoon Hoo, Choi Yu Bin)

1374
01:01:56,117 --> 01:01:57,157
Cooking?

1375
01:01:57,987 --> 01:01:59,327
I'll cook eggs.

1376
01:01:59,687 --> 01:02:01,326
She joined the cooking team.

1377
01:02:01,327 --> 01:02:02,427
This is how...

1378
01:02:03,127 --> 01:02:05,026
- Meat?
- Meat? I'll make pasta.

1379
01:02:05,027 --> 01:02:09,667
(The cooking team is formed quickly around Yoon Hoo.)

1380
01:02:09,937 --> 01:02:12,936
- My gosh.
- They're quick thinkers.

1381
01:02:12,937 --> 01:02:14,176
(The dads are taken back by their daughters' speed.)

1382
01:02:14,177 --> 01:02:17,507
As soon as Yoon Hoo made up his mind, two people followed.

1383
01:02:18,177 --> 01:02:19,346
(He spots something.)

1384
01:02:19,347 --> 01:02:22,076
Min Soo is sitting arrogantly.

1385
01:02:22,077 --> 01:02:23,176
Look at his posture.

1386
01:02:23,177 --> 01:02:24,446
Let me have some snacks.

1387
01:02:24,447 --> 01:02:25,486
(His confidence is boosted thanks to his son.)

1388
01:02:25,487 --> 01:02:27,456
He is finally...

1389
01:02:27,457 --> 01:02:28,716
Before we started,

1390
01:02:28,717 --> 01:02:30,727
we said we could hold each other by the collar.

1391
01:02:31,287 --> 01:02:33,026
I'm quite worried about this.

1392
01:02:33,027 --> 01:02:34,126
(Si Woo's dad suddenly gets angry at his cocky attitude.)

1393
01:02:34,127 --> 01:02:36,126
He scored too many from the start.

1394
01:02:36,127 --> 01:02:37,627
(For how long will he keep his smile?)

1395
01:02:38,997 --> 01:02:43,537
(How did you feel when you became the same team as Yu Bin and Si Woo?)

1396
01:02:45,537 --> 01:02:49,607
I coincidentally became the same team...

1397
01:02:49,777 --> 01:02:53,446
with the two people I was most curious about.

1398
01:02:53,447 --> 01:02:56,747
I wanted to use this chance to get to know them well.

1399
01:02:57,617 --> 01:03:00,687
Yoon Hoo is interested in Si Woo too.

1400
01:03:02,517 --> 01:03:04,686
- Then the three of us...
- The tree?

1401
01:03:04,687 --> 01:03:05,726
- The tree.
- Are you okay with it?

1402
01:03:05,727 --> 01:03:07,026
- Are you okay with it?
- Yes.

1403
01:03:07,027 --> 01:03:08,157
(Jae Seung, Jae Hyuk, and Eun Byul became Team Tree.)

1404
01:03:09,197 --> 01:03:10,597
It was a shame,

1405
01:03:10,827 --> 01:03:12,527
but I still have a lot of time.

1406
01:03:13,127 --> 01:03:15,197
Jae Hyuk isn't assertive.

1407
01:03:17,067 --> 01:03:19,866
I got on the same team as the person...

1408
01:03:19,867 --> 01:03:21,206
I chose for the first impression.

1409
01:03:21,207 --> 01:03:23,607
I got the chance to talk with him.

1410
01:03:24,007 --> 01:03:25,177
- So I was really happy.
- My gosh.

1411
01:03:25,777 --> 01:03:28,147
- It's a chance for Eun Byul.
- That's right.

1412
01:03:29,717 --> 01:03:31,216
Shall we get started?

1413
01:03:31,217 --> 01:03:32,287
- Okay.
- Let's do it.

1414
01:03:33,987 --> 01:03:35,287
How does kimchi fried rice sound?

1415
01:03:35,617 --> 01:03:37,426
- I'm fine with anything.
- Really?

1416
01:03:37,427 --> 01:03:38,487
I'll eat anything happily.

1417
01:03:40,957 --> 01:03:42,227
Do you like eggs?

1418
01:03:42,557 --> 01:03:43,627
Eggs?

1419
01:03:44,067 --> 01:03:45,466
Eggs are a must for kimchi fried rice.

1420
01:03:45,467 --> 01:03:46,827
Okay. Then...

1421
01:03:46,997 --> 01:03:48,266
- shall I make fried eggs?
- Fried eggs?

1422
01:03:48,267 --> 01:03:49,636
- Fried eggs?
- Sounds good.

1423
01:03:49,637 --> 01:03:51,036
- Six?
- Sure.

1424
01:03:51,037 --> 01:03:52,037
(Today's main menu with Assistant Si Woo)

1425
01:03:52,038 --> 01:03:54,636
- Then...
- Kimchi fried rice and steak.

1426
01:03:54,637 --> 01:03:55,937
(Yu Bin's kimchi fried rice and Yoon Hoo's steak)

1427
01:03:56,477 --> 01:03:58,847
Yoon Hoo must be careful with his actions here.

1428
01:03:59,047 --> 01:04:00,047
- Yes.
- That's right.

1429
01:04:00,048 --> 01:04:01,316
- Depending on...
- Exactly.

1430
01:04:01,317 --> 01:04:02,376
- who he talks more to, - Yes.

1431
01:04:02,377 --> 01:04:04,617
- one of them could feel hurt.
- That's right.

1432
01:04:04,987 --> 01:04:06,887
Since there are three in a team,

1433
01:04:07,017 --> 01:04:09,416
- one could feel left out.
- Yes.

1434
01:04:09,417 --> 01:04:10,457
(Mind your actions, Yoon Hoo.)

1435
01:04:11,287 --> 01:04:13,526
How much water should I add?

1436
01:04:13,527 --> 01:04:14,596
(Starting with cooking rice)

1437
01:04:14,597 --> 01:04:15,657
Let me see.

1438
01:04:18,067 --> 01:04:19,927
- That much?
- This much?

1439
01:04:20,297 --> 01:04:22,736
I haven't cooked rice in a long time.

1440
01:04:22,737 --> 01:04:24,507
Do they have instant rice?

1441
01:04:24,567 --> 01:04:25,737
We won't die.

1442
01:04:26,967 --> 01:04:28,877
I have a feeling they'd have instant rice.

1443
01:04:32,647 --> 01:04:35,247
- In here?
- There?

1444
01:04:35,717 --> 01:04:37,647
Si Woo came next to him.

1445
01:04:37,847 --> 01:04:39,317
Next to Hoo.

1446
01:04:39,587 --> 01:04:40,716
I think it's here.

1447
01:04:40,717 --> 01:04:41,787
(Glancing)

1448
01:04:43,587 --> 01:04:45,156
(Yoon Hoo and Si Woo start looking for instant rice.)

1449
01:04:45,157 --> 01:04:46,886
- In here.
- There's none, right?

1450
01:04:46,887 --> 01:04:48,527
- Yes. I don't think there's one.
- I don't think we have it.

1451
01:04:52,997 --> 01:04:54,166
(He finds instant rice.)

1452
01:04:54,167 --> 01:04:55,197
Is that?

1453
01:04:56,567 --> 01:04:58,737
- Amazing.
- I'm glad we found it.

1454
01:05:00,467 --> 01:05:02,737
- Ramyeon...
- Didn't you say you like ramyeon?

1455
01:05:02,877 --> 01:05:03,906
Shall we cook one later?

1456
01:05:03,907 --> 01:05:04,907
- Ramyeon?
- Yes.

1457
01:05:04,908 --> 01:05:06,677
- I'll cook it nicely.
- Okay.

1458
01:05:08,017 --> 01:05:09,017
Let's cook together.

1459
01:05:10,617 --> 01:05:12,216
"Let's cook together."

1460
01:05:12,217 --> 01:05:13,847
Cook together, son.

1461
01:05:13,987 --> 01:05:16,456
What's there to cook together?

1462
01:05:16,457 --> 01:05:18,656
That bothers me.

1463
01:05:18,657 --> 01:05:19,686
(Seeing his daughter flirt for the first time)

1464
01:05:19,687 --> 01:05:20,927
Si Woo is assertive.

1465
01:05:22,127 --> 01:05:23,127
Let's cook together.

1466
01:05:30,867 --> 01:05:32,207
(Surprised)

1467
01:05:32,637 --> 01:05:34,607
Are you supposed to use this much?

1468
01:05:34,837 --> 01:05:36,076
Of course.

1469
01:05:36,077 --> 01:05:37,077
Of course.

1470
01:05:38,547 --> 01:05:40,376
Can you really do it?

1471
01:05:40,377 --> 01:05:41,816
Hold on.

1472
01:05:41,817 --> 01:05:44,417
- Yu Bin.
- Is Yu Bin there just to cook?

1473
01:05:44,817 --> 01:05:47,017
Her ears must be listening to everything they say.

1474
01:05:51,287 --> 01:05:52,957
I couldn't help but pay attention to them.

1475
01:05:53,227 --> 01:05:56,257
I wanted to be on the same team as Hoo,

1476
01:05:56,397 --> 01:05:59,266
but Si Woo kept making jokes at him...

1477
01:05:59,267 --> 01:06:02,367
and talked and asked him stuff.

1478
01:06:02,797 --> 01:06:05,666
I didn't let it show, but I wasn't too happy.

1479
01:06:05,667 --> 01:06:06,966
- Of course.
- Exactly.

1480
01:06:06,967 --> 01:06:08,037
She would.

1481
01:06:09,737 --> 01:06:12,646
Did anyone pull each other's hair in Season One?

1482
01:06:12,647 --> 01:06:13,806
No.

1483
01:06:13,807 --> 01:06:15,516
- They didn't go that far.
- I see.

1484
01:06:15,517 --> 01:06:16,877
They came close to it, though.

1485
01:06:18,687 --> 01:06:21,687
(Meanwhile, Yoon Hoo's steak is grilled nicely.)

1486
01:06:25,157 --> 01:06:26,787
It is quite bloody.

1487
01:06:27,487 --> 01:06:28,697
You should try it.

1488
01:06:29,357 --> 01:06:31,327
(Eyes fixed)

1489
01:06:32,127 --> 01:06:33,427
Could the meat...

1490
01:06:33,667 --> 01:06:34,997
Wait, let me cut it.

1491
01:06:37,637 --> 01:06:38,637
(Glancing)

1492
01:06:45,507 --> 01:06:47,206
Anyway,

1493
01:06:47,207 --> 01:06:50,777
it seemed that two of them expressed their interest in me.

1494
01:06:51,147 --> 01:06:53,917
But if I gave it to one first,

1495
01:06:54,417 --> 01:06:56,086
the other...

1496
01:06:56,087 --> 01:06:58,887
could feel upset.

1497
01:07:00,387 --> 01:07:03,527
That kept weighing on my mind.

1498
01:07:05,497 --> 01:07:07,426
Who will he...

1499
01:07:07,427 --> 01:07:08,836
- give the meat to first?
- Yes.

1500
01:07:08,837 --> 01:07:09,936
Let's see.

1501
01:07:09,937 --> 01:07:12,137
- Who will have it first?
- Hoo, be smart.

1502
01:07:12,207 --> 01:07:13,266
- Just...
- Let's see.

1503
01:07:13,267 --> 01:07:14,606
Just let them eat on their own.

1504
01:07:14,607 --> 01:07:15,877
- Don't give it to anyone.
- Put it in your mouth.

1505
01:07:19,247 --> 01:07:20,747
- I...
- I think I'm bad at cooking.

1506
01:07:21,817 --> 01:07:23,016
- Now that I'm cooking, - No, you can do it.

1507
01:07:23,017 --> 01:07:24,386
- I think I'm bad at it.
- You can do it.

1508
01:07:24,387 --> 01:07:26,047
It looks rather strange.

1509
01:07:26,647 --> 01:07:28,157
No, I think it looks all right.

1510
01:07:28,587 --> 01:07:29,587
Okay.

1511
01:07:37,697 --> 01:07:38,727
(Glancing)

1512
01:07:38,997 --> 01:07:40,026
(Glancing)

1513
01:07:40,027 --> 01:07:41,297
He's glancing left and right.

1514
01:07:41,997 --> 01:07:45,237
He might start hyperventilating.

1515
01:07:45,507 --> 01:07:48,577
His eyes have been moving busily since just now.

1516
01:07:49,107 --> 01:07:51,347
It must be hard for him.

1517
01:07:58,387 --> 01:07:59,487
The meat...

1518
01:08:00,187 --> 01:08:01,416
The meat...

1519
01:08:01,417 --> 01:08:02,587
- The meat.
- My gosh.

1520
01:08:02,987 --> 01:08:04,086
(Who will have the first bite?)

1521
01:08:04,087 --> 01:08:05,927
Hold on.

1522
01:08:06,487 --> 01:08:08,157
- Hold on.
- Just put it down.

1523
01:08:08,857 --> 01:08:09,997
The meat...

1524
01:08:12,267 --> 01:08:14,596
(Si Woo?)

1525
01:08:14,597 --> 01:08:17,137
- No!
- Hey.

1526
01:08:18,167 --> 01:08:20,266
I'll go and let them try the meat.

1527
01:08:20,267 --> 01:08:22,036
- Okay.
- I'll experiment on them.

1528
01:08:22,037 --> 01:08:24,076
I'll go and let them try the meat.

1529
01:08:24,077 --> 01:08:25,777
- Okay.
- I'll experiment on them.

1530
01:08:27,877 --> 01:08:29,577
- I'll go and let them try the meat?
- I'll go and let them try the meat.

1531
01:08:30,047 --> 01:08:31,316
(That's absurd.)

1532
01:08:31,317 --> 01:08:32,317
He's going to the other team.

1533
01:08:32,318 --> 01:08:34,486
Hoo, your first choice was Yu Bin.

1534
01:08:34,487 --> 01:08:36,516
You should give it to Yu Bin first.

1535
01:08:36,517 --> 01:08:38,356
He should let those working with him...

1536
01:08:38,357 --> 01:08:40,226
- try it first.
- Good job.

1537
01:08:40,227 --> 01:08:42,227
- Good job, my son.
- He made a wise choice.

1538
01:08:42,827 --> 01:08:43,827
Good job.

1539
01:08:44,727 --> 01:08:46,867
(Rushing)

1540
01:08:48,897 --> 01:08:50,496
Why isn't he letting us try it?

1541
01:08:50,497 --> 01:08:51,607
I know, right?

1542
01:08:53,407 --> 01:08:55,937
They were secretly waiting for it too.

1543
01:08:58,647 --> 01:09:00,107
How is everything?

1544
01:09:00,907 --> 01:09:03,217
Please check if the meat is...

1545
01:09:03,477 --> 01:09:04,646
cooked right.

1546
01:09:04,647 --> 01:09:05,686
- Thank you.
- Here.

1547
01:09:05,687 --> 01:09:08,856
(The first bite goes to Jae Hyuk.)

1548
01:09:08,857 --> 01:09:10,116
It's cooked just nicely, right?

1549
01:09:10,117 --> 01:09:11,387
- I like it.
- It's cooked enough?

1550
01:09:12,227 --> 01:09:13,227
It's tasty.

1551
01:09:14,257 --> 01:09:16,596
I let Jae Hyuk, my roommate,

1552
01:09:16,597 --> 01:09:19,067
taste it first.

